{"article_id":"Oja0HAA7W0qG7jXP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Trump ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"who has called the Iran nuclear agreement the \" worst deal ever , \"","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"has found a way","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"to distance himself from it symbolically","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"without causing an immediate rupture with Iran or U.S. allies","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"who want to keep the accord in place .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"Trump announced Friday his refusal","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"to re-certify Iran 's compliance with the 2015 agreement ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"which prevents Iran from trying to develop nuclear weapons for at least a decade in exchange for relief from international economic sanctions .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"But Trump will not ask Congress to re-impose sanctions right away , a move","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"that could prompt Iran to back out of the deal and resume its nuclear development program","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"-much to the dismay of other world powers","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"who signed onto the deal along with the U.S .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Congress requires the president to certify Iran 's compliance with the agreement every three months .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Despite Trump 's refusal to do so this time ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"there are many reasons","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"why Congress may be unwilling to take punitive action against Iran on its own .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"For one thing , U.N. inspectors say","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Iran is in compliance ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"and there may be little appetite for a new crisis","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"involving nuclear weapons on top of the mounting tensions with North Korea ' over its nuclear program .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"More :","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"What 's at stake","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"if U.S. scraps Iran deal ?","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Another North Korea crisis ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"French president says","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Analysis :","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"Trump 's U.N. trip sets up showdown with Iran and North Korea over nukes","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"More :","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"Uncertainty over Iran nuclear agreement could heighten economic tensions with Europe","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"In addition , the deal has strong support among businesses","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"eager to sign deals with oil-rich Iran .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Boeing has a $ 3 billion contract","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"to provide commercial aircraft .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"Members of Trump ' s own administration ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"including Defense Secretary Jim Mattis ,","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"have lobbied against undermining the agreement ,","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"which was also signed by China , France , Germany , Russia and the United Kingdom .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"\" If we can confirm","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"that Iran is living by the agreement ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"if we can determine","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"that this is in our best interest ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"then clearly we should stay with it , ''","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"Mattis recently told Congress .","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"Trump , Israel and other critics of the deal ,","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"signed by President Obama ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"question","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"whether Iran can cheat","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"and secretly develop nuclear weapons","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"without detection ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"an argument","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"disputed by U.N. inspectors .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"These critics also complain","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"that the lifting of sanctions gives Iran billions of dollars in new funds","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"to sponsor terrorist organizations around the world","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"and develop ballistic missiles ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"which are not covered under the accord .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"While many in Congress share that view ,","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"so long as they refrain from imposing new sanctions ,","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"the agreement would stay in place ,","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"said Michael Rubin , an analyst at the American Enterprise Institute .","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"\" Decertification isn ' t synonymous with walking away from the deal , \"","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"If Congress imposed sanctions ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"prompting Iran to renege on the deal ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"`` that ' s a twofer \" for the Iranians ,","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"Rubin said :","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"Iran has already obtained benefits from the lifting of sanctions","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"and now could restart its nuclear program as well","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"- and blame it all on the United States .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"New sanctions would endanger billions of dollars in potential investments","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"that have already been negotiated .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"It would also anger U.S. allies ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"including France ,","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"which has urged the U.S. not to discard the nuclear deal .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"\" Proponents of the agreement are saying","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"American credibility is at stake , especially with European allies , \"","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"Rubin said .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Rather than push to scuttle the agreement ,","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"Trump plans to call for new negotiations","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"to modify it .","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"Fellow critics have urged the U.S. and its allies to force Iran to accept modifications , such as tighter restrictions on missile tests and funding radical militias in the Middle East .","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"That approach is a long shot .","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"The Iranian government has repeatedly ruled out renegotiating any part of the agreement .","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"\" It will be a great pity","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"if this agreement were to be destroyed by rogue newcomers to the world of politics , \"","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"Even Trump is `` not particularly optimistic ''","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"that the agreement can be fixed ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"Secretary of State Rex Tillerson said .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"`` We may not be able to fix the deal . ''","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"Trump said Friday","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"if Iran refuses to modify the agreement ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"he 'll formally terminate it","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"and order sanctions","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"slapped back on Iran .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"It ' s possible that the White House could work with Congress","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"to threaten severe sanctions as a way","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to get Iran to agree to renegotiate ,","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"said Luke Coffey , an analyst at the Heritage Foundation .","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"But he also acknowledged","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"that is unlikely .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"\" I don ' t see","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"why Iran would want to renegotiate anything","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"since the deal is so favorably on their side , \"","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"he said .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":150,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":112,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":110,"right":111